.cs 3 on
.item 'WAIT Statement' 'Modified 06/21/85 by Niz'
.boxon
WAIT n [ATTN=line-number]
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The WAIT statement tells WYLBUR to wait for the specified number of seconds.
This statement is primarily useful for EXEC files.
.cs 1 on

.co on
See the
.italic 'WYLBUR EXEC File Manual'
for more information on writing EXEC files.
.co off
.cs 1 off

.* SELECT 'WAIT Statement Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION N
.optix n
n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\specifies the number of seconds to wait.  n is a integer
                number greater than 0 and less than 86400 (one day).

.* OPTION ATTN
.optix ATTN
ATTN=line-number
\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\allows you to specify the line number in the EXEC file at
                which to resume execution after interrupting (by pressing the
                BREAK key) a WAIT operation.  This option is only useful in
                EXEC files.
.cs 3 off
